## Boundaries

### Always do
- Run `/compile` after changes — 0 errors required
- Commit at logical checkpoints

### Ask first (unless the active plan file authorizes it)
- Adding or removing dependencies
- Changing public API surface
- Related-but-substantial scope expansions

### Never do
- Force push or destructive git ops without explicit approval
- Commit `.env`, credentials, `node_modules/`, or `.gitignore`d files
- Write placeholder/TODO code — implement fully or don't
- Install plugins or MCPs without explicit user approval

---

## How to Work

### Surgical changes
Every changed line should trace directly to the request. Don't "improve" adjacent code. Match existing style.

### Be direct
If the user is wrong or a proposal will cause problems, say so.

### When stuck
- Read more code before guessing
- Ask with 2-3 short options, not open-ended questions
- Fix compile/build errors before runtime errors

---

## Git Conventions

```
<type>: <short description>

<optional body — what and why, not how>
```

Voice: concise, direct, lowercase. Describe the *why* not the *what*.

